article_title: As Obamacare deadline approaches, Florida leads nation in enrollment for health plans
article_text:
Open enrollment began on Nov. 1 and closes Sunday

More than 1.6 million Floridians have signed up for coverage

Penalty for going uninsured in 2016 rises to $695 per adult

article_metadata.news-keywords: Affordable Care Act, Obamacare, Health Insurance Market Place, open enrollment, Florida, Miami, Miami-Dade, uninsured, health insurance, Medicaid, hospitals
article_metadata.description: In all his years working as a high-altitude tree trimmer, David Mendoza said he never had a serious accident, much less with a chainsaw, like the one that nearly claimed his left hand on Jan. 18 as he tried to remove a fallen tree from atop the garage of a Coral Gables home.
